bug.short_desc: Font settings of ibus are ignored (on non-Gnome desktops like Xfce, ...)
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1229129 font-settings-of-ibus-are-ignored-xfce.png
I installed Fedora-Workstation-netinst-x86_64-25-1.3.iso in qemu and then installed other desktops using dnf.
Then I used ibus on the Xfce desktop.
Changing the font does not work (This worked in Fedora 24).
See the attached screenshot.
I did choose “Liberation Sans Regular” in the rather big size 24, but the candidate list is still being displayed in a small font.
In the terminal one can see that the dconf setting is correct.

There are two issues.
For Fedora 25, GTK 3.22 dropped the Pango format and need this patch: https://github.com/ibus/ibus/commit/aacf5adbba9b9b34a1ec07005e670d209513fb5b
For Fedora 24, IBus didn't build with GTK 3.20 or later and need to rebuild without any changes. I thought releng would rebuilt it and forgot it.
